
Building plugins:

    In Makefile
        Change MAYA_LOCATION
        Change INSTALL_LOCATION
        Change PLUGIN_NAME

    Get plugin ids
        Get Maya plugin ids from Autodesk and set it in utils.h

    Run make in command prompt
        This should produce plugin.so


In Maya:scpriptEditor:python:

    cmds.file(new=1, f=1)
    cmds.unloadPlugin("plugin")

    cmds.loadPlugin("mayaPlugins/*.so")

    cmds.select(<mesh with skinCluster>)
    psdNode = cmds.poseSpaceCommand(create='poseDeformerNewName')

    cmds.select(<mesh with skinCluster>)
    dupMesh = cmds.duplicate()
    <edit dupMesh vertices to set it up as pose mesh>
    cmds.select(dupMesh)

    poseIndex = cmds.poseSpaceCommand(addPose=psdNode)
